@node double "Double game"

@{b}Double game@{ub}

When you win a hand you have a choice to bet your winnings at a
game of 'Double or Nothing'.

Press 'NO' collects your winnings. (No Double game)

Press 'YES' and five new cards will be dealt, the first face up,
is the computer's card and the one you must top. The other four are
face down and you must simply pick a card at chance. Aces are high.

If your card is HIGHER than the computer's you've just doubled your
winnings. You can then choose to play again or collect your money.
You can double for as long as you wish, or more likely, until you lose.

If your card is LOWER you lose your winnings. The other three cards
will be revealed. There is no guarantee of a winning card among the
four cards you are dealt -- But with +V3.0 there is a new feature called
the @{"'STAR GAME'" link stargame} that will award you a goldstar if you manage to pick
the HIGHEST card when losing, when you have three stars
the STAR GAME is activated.

If your cards are EQUAL you keep your money and get the choice
of playing again or collecting your money.

ex. You get a 'Three of a kind' with a $5 bet = $15
    Double once and win = $15 X 2 = $30
    Double a second time = $30 X 2 = $60

My personal record is 7 doubles at a FLUSH with a $5 bet.
$30 x 2 x 2 x 2 x 2 x 2 x 2 x 2 = $3840.

@endnode

@node acehi "ACES HIGH"

@{b}ACES HIGH@{ub}

Bonus feature:
This is not a standard poker-variation but a thing i made up myself.
