@node stats "Statistics"

@{b}Statistics@{ub}

Press the button 'Stats' on the main screen and you will see a screen
with a wast array of statistics about your current game.

THE GRAPH:
Displays your money over time. The grey horizontal line shows
your start amount (usually $100). Profits are shown in GREEN and losses
are displayed in RED. The graph will show max 2500 games.

THE WINNING-HANDS TABLE:
Shows the number of games won of each @{"Winning-hand" link rules} in numbers and
frequency. From V3.0 the syntax of frequency is 1/x instead of the previous
and quite pointless system of: 12/293, 79/467 etc...


    PLAYER: Your @{"Log-in" link login} name.
      CASH: Your current funds.
 @{"BANKROLL:" link bankroll} Your lifetime balance.
    PROFIT: Your profit/gain over the start-sum in %.
       TOP: Highest amount achived during game.

     GAMES: Number of hands you've played.
       WON: Games won in numbers and %.
      LOST: Games lost in numbers and %.

  @{b}STREAKS:@{ub} @{"Streak display" link streaks}
      WIN: Highest number of consecutively won hands.
     LOSE: Highest number of consecutively lost hands.
  DOUBLES: Highest number of consecutively won doubles and it`s pay-off.

  @{b}DOUBLES:@{ub} @{"Double game" link double}
      BET: Total amount invested in the 'Double game'.
      WON: Total amount paid-out from the 'Double game'.
 WON/LOST: Total number(s) of won & lost hands in the 'Double game'.
 YOUR AVG: Your average card picked in the 'Double game'.
 COMP AVG: Computers average card given in the 'Double game'.

ACES HIGH: Number of @{"ACES HIGH" link acehi} bonus-games played.

 STARGAME: Number of @{"STAR GAMES" link stargame} played.

 GAMETIME: Time elapsed during your current game (hh.mm.ss).

