@node bankroll "BANK ROLL"

@{b}BANK ROLL@{ub} (V3.0)

When you log-in an account will be created in that name.

This account will keep track of your lifetime balance and is always shown
left of the cash display, also at log-in and on the statistics-screen.
The account is updated when you cash-out, lose or restart.

Note that this is ONLY a record of history, you borrow $100 from me every
time you play, so if you cash out the first time with $150 your bank-roll
would be +$50.

The system can handle up to 100 diffrent accounts, if you exceed this limit
any new accounts will NOT be created but everything else should work fine.

If you have reached the 100 limit or for any other reason, like a great
loss, would wish to clear the accounts there is an option that will
completely erase all records:

Log-in commands:
BANKZERO - Clear ALL bank-roll accounts.

The bank-roll was suggested by Glen A. Blair, Las Vegas. However i could
not meet his request to resume a game with the current bank-roll as ACTIVE
funds, for three reasons:
1. This is a VideoPoker-machine simulator, cashing-out means cashing-OUT.
2. You can't play with NEGATIVE funds, just recording profit would be wrong.
3. A big profit-account would mess up the high-score table, as you would be
   entered every time you play.



@endnode
